DOM:
1) Create a new element (single,multiple)
2) Append a element inside the parent code
   Add the element at the end
3) InsertBefore (): insert a new node before an existing node or child note of a specific parent code
---this requires a reference to both the new node and the existing node you want to insert before.

 <div id="a">
            <h1>Sweety</h1>
            <h1 id=”b”>Ammu</h1>
        </div>
        <div id="b">
            <h2>Cherry</h2>
            <h2>Chotu</h2>
        </div>
    <script>
        let n=document.createelement("h2")
        n.textContent="Swathi"

        let p=document.getElementById("a")
        let l=document.getElementById("b")
        p.insertBefore(n,l)
        console.log(n)
    </script>

O/P:
 
Ex:2
 <body>
        <div id = "a">
            <h1 id = "c">cherry</h1>
            <h1 id = "r">chandu</h1>
        </div>
        <div id = "b">
            <h2>chotu</h2>
            <h2>chintu</h2>
        </div>
        
        <script>
    
            let s = document.createElement("h2")
            s.textContent = "Swathi"
    
            let n = document.createElement("h2")
            n.textContent = "Ammu"
    
    
            let p = document.getElementById('a')
            let l = document.getElementById('r')
            p.insertBefore(n,l)
            console.log(p)
    
            let q = document.getElementById('c')
            p.insertBefore(s,q)
            
        </script>   
    </body>
        
